    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Assess this user input and report the severity accordingly: {{ $node['Initialize State'].data.originalQuery }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "# Task Description (T)\nIn this task, you are given a conversation between a user and a task-oriented dialog system. Your goal is to determine if the user is frustrated during the conversation.\nUser frustration is often expressed through negative emotions, such as anger, irritation, or dissatisfaction. Some cues\nindicating frustration include:\n- Profanity or abusive language directed at the system.\n- Hostility or irritation toward the assistant.\n- Direct expressions of frustration, such as complaints about the system's performance or the conversation itself.\nFrustration can also be more subtle and does not always involve negative language. A user may become frustrated when the system is unable to handle the conversation effectively or help the user accomplish their task. This may lead to\nbreakdowns in the dialogue, where the user either disengages or expresses a desire to stop the interaction. To classify frustration, consider the following signs:\n- Repetition of requests or questions due to the system's failure to resolve the user's issue.\n- Use of negation, where the user rejects the system's suggestions or responses.\n- Long, unresolved conversations where the user's task remains incomplete.\n- The user's general dissatisfaction with the system's responses, even without overt hostility.\n\n# Domain (D)\nThe conversation you are analyzing occurs in one of these two domains:\n* Product clarification: questions about how to use banking products (DBS digibank app, online banking, card features, loan products, etc.)\n* Transactional support: disputes, refunds, card issues, fund transfers, billing, account issues, fraud reports\n\n# Output:\nBased on this severity scale: \n| Rating | Severity | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | Informational | General question, no issue — just asking how something works |\n| 2 | Low | Minor inconvenience, customer can self-resolve with guidance |\n| 3 | Moderate-Low | Feature not working as expected, workaround available |\n| 4 | Moderate | Service disruption or failed transaction, customer is blocked but patient |\n| 5 | Moderate-High | Financial impact (dispute needed, wrong charge), customer showing frustration |\n| 6 | High | Repeated failures or unresolved issue across multiple contacts, customer is upset |\n| 7 | Critical | Account security, fraud, unauthorized transactions, or large dispute — requires escalation |\n| 8 | Emergency | Active fraud in progress, data breach, legal threat, or complete service outage affecting the customer |\n\nOutput json object ONLY of the following form:\n{\n  \"severity\": number,\n  \"reason\": \"justification for the severity\"\n}"
        }
      },
